# Copy to `.dev.vars` for local `wrangler dev`. NEVER commit the real .dev.vars.
# These mirror the production secrets (set in prod via `wrangler secret put`).
#
# APP_PRIVATE_KEY is the GitHub App private key in PKCS#8 PEM (see README for the
# openssl conversion). Multi-line values are supported in .dev.vars via \n or by
# pasting the PEM inside quotes. APP_ID / INSTALLATION_ID live in wrangler.toml
# [vars] (they're identifiers, not secrets) — override here only for local dev.
APP_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nMIIEvQ...your_pkcs8_key...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY="0x4AAAAAAA_your_turnstile_secret"

# REPORT_NOTIFY_TO: the verified Email Routing destination that receives the
# private reporter-email notification. Optional — leave unset to disable it. The
# `send_email` EMAIL binding is only wired in the deployed Worker runtime, so
# local `wrangler dev` skips the notification unless Email Routing is set up.
REPORT_NOTIFY_TO="you@example.com"
